  <steps>
    <step num="0">Pour the red wine and water into a medium pan. Season with salt. </step>
    <step num="1">Bring the mixture to a boil and add the spaghetti. </step>
    <step num="2">Cook until most of the red wine is absorbed by the pasta, 8-10 minutes. </step>
    <step num="3">Transfer the pasta to a medium bowl. </step>
    <step num="4">Melt the butter in the same skillet over medium heat. Add the garlic, pine nuts, and red pepper flakes. </step>
    <step num="5">Cook the sauce until the butter starts to brown, then add the pasta. </step>
    <step num="6">Mix the sauce and pasta together. </step>
    <step num="7">Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. </step>
    <step num="8">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
